# AI Standards

Read the applicable standard from `docs/standards/ai/` before modifying agent, persona, provider, or memory code.

## Key Standards

- **Agent architecture** (`docs/standards/ai/agent-architecture.md`): pipeline design, vtable responsibilities, retry/fallback, temperature guidance
- **Prompt engineering** (`docs/standards/ai/prompt-engineering.md`): system prompt structure, persona composition, RAG patterns, context window management
- **Conversation design** (`docs/standards/ai/conversation-design.md`): response patterns, channel-aware behavior, intent routing, error states
- **Hallucination prevention** (`docs/standards/ai/hallucination-prevention.md`): grounding hierarchy, tool output integrity, memory attribution
- **Human-in-the-loop** (`docs/standards/ai/human-in-the-loop.md`): approval tiers, security policy integration, confirmation flow
- **Citation and sourcing** (`docs/standards/ai/citation-and-sourcing.md`): source tiers, freshness rules, confidence mapping
- **Evaluation** (`docs/standards/ai/evaluation.md`): quality dimensions, golden-set testing, per-provider metrics
- **Disclosure** (`docs/standards/ai/disclosure.md`): AI identity disclosure rules
- **Responsible AI** (`docs/standards/ai/responsible-ai.md`): model governance

## Critical Rules

- Agent loop orchestrates; providers are stateless; tools never call providers directly
- Every provider invocation is observable via `hu_observer_t` (tokens, latency, model, error)
- Persona composition: identity + traits + channel overlay + examples + memory context
- Tool results are highest-trust data; preserve numerical precision, never fabricate output
- Max 2 retries per provider, then fallback; max depth 10 for tool dispatch loops
- Never expose system internals to users (error codes, model names, token counts, tool JSON)
- `HU_IS_TEST` guards for any provider calls or tool executions in tests
